Definition: deviating from what is considered moral or right or proper or good
Example: depraved criminals; a perverted sense of loyalty; the reprobate conduct of a gambling aristocrat
Synonyms: noun, attribute, depravity, perverse, perverseness, perversity, perverted, reprobate, person, deviating, from, what, is, considered, moral, or, right, proper, good, criminals, a, sense, of, loyalty, the, conduct, gambling, aristocrat
Category: adj.all
